Further Note: Thru 80+ years of reprintings, the Loeb edition here gives Crassus "not quite <I>twenty</I> years of age". The mistake made it thru my own proofreadings, but not past the sharp eyes of Robert Greaves, who noticed that according to Plutarch himself
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Crassus*.html#17.2
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,5,WIDTH,140)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(17.2)
	</A>
